115        public void test0001() throws JavaScriptModelException {
116                IJavaScriptUnit sourceUnit = getCompilationUnit("Converter" , "src", "test0001", "Test.js"); //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-3$ //$NON-NLS-4$
117                char[] source = sourceUnit.getSource().toCharArray();
118                ASTNode result = runConversion(AST.JLS3, sourceUnit, false);
119                
120                // check that we have the right tree
121                JavaScriptUnit unit = this.ast.newJavaScriptUnit();
122                PackageDeclaration packageDeclaration = this.ast.newPackageDeclaration();
123                packageDeclaration.setName(this.ast.newSimpleName("test0001"));//$NON-NLS-1$
124                unit.setPackage(packageDeclaration);
125                ImportDeclaration importDeclaration = this.ast.newImportDeclaration();
126                QualifiedName name = 
127                        this.ast.newQualifiedName(
128                                this.ast.newSimpleName("java"),//$NON-NLS-1$
129                                this.ast.newSimpleName("util"));//$NON-NLS-1$
130                importDeclaration.setName(name);
131                importDeclaration.setOnDemand(true);
132                unit.imports().add(importDeclaration);
133                TypeDeclaration type = this.ast.newTypeDeclaration();
134                type.setInterface(false);
135                type.modifiers().add(this.ast.newModifier(Modifier.ModifierKeyword.PUBLIC_KEYWORD));
136                type.setName(this.ast.newSimpleName("Test"));//$NON-NLS-1$
137                FunctionDeclaration methodDeclaration = this.ast.newFunctionDeclaration();
138                methodDeclaration.setConstructor(false);
139                methodDeclaration.modifiers().add(this.ast.newModifier(Modifier.ModifierKeyword.PUBLIC_KEYWORD));
140                methodDeclaration.modifiers().add(this.ast.newModifier(Modifier.ModifierKeyword.STATIC_KEYWORD));
141                methodDeclaration.setName(this.ast.newSimpleName("main"));//$NON-NLS-1$
142                methodDeclaration.setReturnType2(this.ast.newPrimitiveType(PrimitiveType.VOID));
143                SingleVariableDeclaration variableDeclaration = this.ast.newSingleVariableDeclaration();
144                variableDeclaration.setType(this.ast.newArrayType(this.ast.newSimpleType(this.ast.newSimpleName("String"))));//$NON-NLS-1$
145                variableDeclaration.setName(this.ast.newSimpleName("args"));//$NON-NLS-1$
146                methodDeclaration.parameters().add(variableDeclaration);
147                org.eclipse.wst.jsdt.core.dom.Block block = this.ast.newBlock();
148                FunctionInvocation methodInvocation = this.ast.newFunctionInvocation();
149                name = 
150                        this.ast.newQualifiedName(
151                                this.ast.newSimpleName("System"),//$NON-NLS-1$
152                                this.ast.newSimpleName("out"));//$NON-NLS-1$
153                methodInvocation.setExpression(name);
154                methodInvocation.setName(this.ast.newSimpleName("println")); //$NON-NLS-1$
155                InfixExpression infixExpression = this.ast.newInfixExpression();
156                infixExpression.setOperator(InfixExpression.Operator.PLUS);
157                StringLiteral literal = this.ast.newStringLiteral();
158                literal.setLiteralValue("Hello");//$NON-NLS-1$
159                infixExpression.setLeftOperand(literal);
160                literal = this.ast.newStringLiteral();
161                literal.setLiteralValue(" world");//$NON-NLS-1$
162                infixExpression.setRightOperand(literal);//$NON-NLS-1$
163                methodInvocation.arguments().add(infixExpression);
164                ExpressionStatement expressionStatement = this.ast.newExpressionStatement(methodInvocation);
165                block.statements().add(expressionStatement);
166                methodDeclaration.setBody(block);
167                type.bodyDeclarations().add(methodDeclaration);
168                unit.types().add(type);
169                assertTrue("Both AST trees should be identical", result.subtreeMatch(new ASTMatcher(), unit));//$NON-NLS-1$
170                String expected =
171                        "package test0001;\n" + 
172                        "import java.util.*;\n" + 
173                        "public class Test {\n" + 
174                        "        public static void main(String[] args) {\n" + 
175                        "                System.out.println(\"Hello\" + \" world\");\n" + 
176                        "        }\n" + 
177                        "}";
178                checkSourceRange(result, expected, source);
179        }

184        public void test0002() throws JavaScriptModelException {
185                IJavaScriptUnit sourceUnit = getCompilationUnit("Converter" , "src", "test0002", "Test.js"); //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-3$ //$NON-NLS-4$
186                char[] source = sourceUnit.getSource().toCharArray();
187                ASTNode result = runConversion(AST.JLS3, sourceUnit, false);
188                ASTNode expression = getASTNodeToCompare((JavaScriptUnit) result);
189                assertNotNull("Expression should not be null", expression); //$NON-NLS-1$
190                ClassInstanceCreation classInstanceCreation = this.ast.newClassInstanceCreation();
191                classInstanceCreation.setType(this.ast.newSimpleType(this.ast.newSimpleName("Object"))); //$NON-NLS-1$

193                checkSourceRange(expression, "new Object()", source); //$NON-NLS-1$
194        }

2761        /**
2762         * Multiple local declaration => VariabledeclarationStatement
2763         */
2764        public void test0124() throws JavaScriptModelException {
2765                IJavaScriptUnit sourceUnit = getCompilationUnit("Converter" , "src", "test0124", "Test.js"); //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-3$ //$NON-NLS-4$
2766                char[] source = sourceUnit.getSource().toCharArray();
2767                ASTNode result = runConversion(AST.JLS3, sourceUnit, false);
2768                ASTNode node = getASTNode((JavaScriptUnit) result, 0, 0, 0);
2769                assertNotNull("Expression should not be null", node); //$NON-NLS-1$
2770                VariableDeclarationFragment fragment = this.ast.newVariableDeclarationFragment();
2771                fragment.setName(this.ast.newSimpleName("x"));//$NON-NLS-1$
2772                NumberLiteral literal = this.ast.newNumberLiteral();
2773                literal.setToken("10");//$NON-NLS-1$
2774                fragment.setInitializer(literal);
2775                fragment.setExtraDimensions(0);
2776                VariableDeclarationStatement statement = this.ast.newVariableDeclarationStatement(fragment);
2777                fragment = this.ast.newVariableDeclarationFragment();
2778                fragment.setName(this.ast.newSimpleName("z"));//$NON-NLS-1$
2779                fragment.setInitializer(this.ast.newNullLiteral());
2780                fragment.setExtraDimensions(1);
2781                statement.fragments().add(fragment);
2782                fragment = this.ast.newVariableDeclarationFragment();
2783                fragment.setName(this.ast.newSimpleName("i"));//$NON-NLS-1$
2784                fragment.setExtraDimensions(0);
2785                statement.fragments().add(fragment);
2786                fragment = this.ast.newVariableDeclarationFragment();
2787                fragment.setName(this.ast.newSimpleName("j"));//$NON-NLS-1$
2788                fragment.setExtraDimensions(2);
2789                statement.fragments().add(fragment);
2790                statement.setType(this.ast.newPrimitiveType(PrimitiveType.INT));
2791                assertTrue("Both AST trees should be identical", statement.subtreeMatch(new ASTMatcher(), node));                //$NON-NLS-1$
2792                VariableDeclarationFragment[] fragments = (VariableDeclarationFragment[])((VariableDeclarationStatement) node).fragments().toArray(new VariableDeclarationFragment[4]);
2793                assertTrue("fragments.length != 4", fragments.length == 4); //$NON-NLS-1$
2794                checkSourceRange(fragments[0], "x= 10", source);//$NON-NLS-1$
2795                checkSourceRange(fragments[1], "z[] = null", source);//$NON-NLS-1$
2796                checkSourceRange(fragments[2], "i", source);//$NON-NLS-1$
2797                checkSourceRange(fragments[3], "j[][]", source);//$NON-NLS-1$
2798                checkSourceRange(node, "int x= 10, z[] = null, i, j[][];", source);//$NON-NLS-1$
2799        }

8907         */
8908        public void test0362() throws JavaScriptModelException {
8909                IJavaScriptUnit sourceUnit = getCompilationUnit("Converter" , "src", "test0362", "Test.js"); //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$ //$NON-NLS-3$ //$NON-NLS-4$
8910                char[] source = sourceUnit.getSource().toCharArray();
8911                ASTNode result = runConversion(AST.JLS3, sourceUnit, false);
8912                ASTNode node = getASTNode((JavaScriptUnit) result, 0, 0, 0);
8913                assertNotNull("Expression should not be null", node); //$NON-NLS-1$
8914                ForStatement forStatement = this.ast.newForStatement();
8915 
8916                VariableDeclarationFragment iFragment = this.ast.newVariableDeclarationFragment();
8917                iFragment.setName(this.ast.newSimpleName("i")); //$NON-NLS-1$
8918                iFragment.setInitializer(this.ast.newNumberLiteral("0"));//$NON-NLS-1$
8919                VariableDeclarationFragment jFragment = this.ast.newVariableDeclarationFragment();
8920                jFragment.setName(this.ast.newSimpleName("j")); //$NON-NLS-1$
8921                jFragment.setInitializer(this.ast.newNumberLiteral("0"));//$NON-NLS-1$
8922                VariableDeclarationFragment kFragment = this.ast.newVariableDeclarationFragment();
8923                kFragment.setName(this.ast.newSimpleName("k")); //$NON-NLS-1$
8924                kFragment.setInitializer(this.ast.newNumberLiteral("0"));//$NON-NLS-1$
8925 
8926                VariableDeclarationExpression variableDeclarationExpression = this.ast.newVariableDeclarationExpression(iFragment);
8927                variableDeclarationExpression.setType(this.ast.newPrimitiveType(PrimitiveType.INT));
8928                variableDeclarationExpression.fragments().add(jFragment);
8929                variableDeclarationExpression.fragments().add(kFragment);
8930                forStatement.initializers().add(variableDeclarationExpression);
8931 
8932                PostfixExpression iPostfixExpression = this.ast.newPostfixExpression();
8933                iPostfixExpression.setOperand(this.ast.newSimpleName("i"));//$NON-NLS-1$
8934                iPostfixExpression.setOperator(PostfixExpression.Operator.INCREMENT);
8935                forStatement.updaters().add(iPostfixExpression);
8936                
8937                PostfixExpression jPostfixExpression = this.ast.newPostfixExpression();
8938                jPostfixExpression.setOperand(this.ast.newSimpleName("j"));//$NON-NLS-1$
8939                jPostfixExpression.setOperator(PostfixExpression.Operator.INCREMENT);
8940                forStatement.updaters().add(jPostfixExpression);
8941 
8942                PostfixExpression kPostfixExpression = this.ast.newPostfixExpression();
8943                kPostfixExpression.setOperand(this.ast.newSimpleName("k"));//$NON-NLS-1$
8944                kPostfixExpression.setOperator(PostfixExpression.Operator.INCREMENT);
8945                forStatement.updaters().add(kPostfixExpression);
8946 
8947                forStatement.setBody(this.ast.newBlock());
8948                
8949                InfixExpression infixExpression = this.ast.newInfixExpression();
8950                infixExpression.setLeftOperand(this.ast.newSimpleName("i")); //$NON-NLS-1$
8951                infixExpression.setOperator(InfixExpression.Operator.LESS);
8952                infixExpression.setRightOperand(this.ast.newNumberLiteral("10")); //$NON-NLS-1$
8953                forStatement.setExpression(infixExpression);
8954                
8955                assertTrue("Both AST trees should be identical", forStatement.subtreeMatch(new ASTMatcher(), node));                //$NON-NLS-1$
8956                checkSourceRange(node, "for (int i=0, j=0, k=0; i<10 ; i++, j++, k++) {}", source); //$NON-NLS-1$
8957        }
